params.message:
Please set-up the deck as per the labware and liquids set-up. Spin the colony plate down to pellet the cells and decant the liquid media to the appropriate waste prior to placing the plate on the deck.
Place the purple filter columns, column holder and square well block assembly in position 8.

Place the filter and plate assembly into a plate centrifuge and spin at 3000g for 4 mins.
Remove the filter tubes and place the deep well plate containing the filtrate into position 6.
Place a new DW plate with white binding columns in position 3.
Centrifuge at 3000g for 4 mins and discard the flow through to waste. Place back on the deck in position 8.
Empty tip waste and discard appropriately.
Centrifuge at 3000g for 2 mins and discard flow through.

Centrifuge at 3000g for 2 mins and discard flow through.
Centrifuge again at 5600g for 10mins to remove any residual liquid.
Place a 96 well plate into the square well block and place the tubes into the plate. Place back into position 8 on the deck.
Incubate at RT for a minimum of 3 minutes.
Centrifuge at 3000g for 3 mins to elute the DNA
